title: Taco Soup
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion in a large saucepan over medium heat. Blot any excess grease with a paper towel, then add the taco seasoning. Cook for one minute, then add the tomato sauce, diced tomatoes, kidney beans, and one cup water.
Reduce heat to medium-low, and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add the corn and mashed garbanzo beans, and simmer five more minutes.
Serve immediately. Makes six (1 cup) servings.
ingredients: 1 (14.5 ounce) can no salt added tomato sauce
1 (14.5 ounce) diced tomatoes with green chilies
1 (14.5 ounce) dark kidney beans, drained and rinsed
1 cup frozen or canned corn kernels
1/2 cup chickpeas, drained and rinsed, mashed
